I had been in Vietnam, six months, hard to remember exactly.  Ben and I were in charge of an ambush patrol.  We had a new guy.  He wasn't really new.  He spent his year, then another six months with somebody else, then with us.  Ben was on the front end of &quot;our line.&quot;  I was on the back.  Charlie waked in front of us.  The new guy, I can't even remembe his name, stood up and said &quot;stop or I'll shoot.&quot;  Charlie turned and killed him.  I can only think that it was a suicide.  We killed Charlie  It was sad - just sad.  That's PTSD.<br><br>
